Your package vifm failed to build from source in current rawhide.
http://koji.fedoraproject.org/koji/taskinfo?taskID=12876872
For details on mass rebuild see https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_24_Mass_Rebuild

This bug appears to have been reported against 'rawhide' during the Fedora 24 development cycle. Changing version to '24'.
More information and reason for this action is here: https://fedoraproject.org/wiki/Fedora_Program_Management/HouseKeeping/Fedora24#Rawhide_Rebase

Created attachment 1139337 Patch to address this issue
This FTBFS is caused by mixing direct installation of docs (make install) into %{_pkgdocdir} and installation of docs through "%doc <relative path>".
The patch in the attachment (against fedora git/master) contains how I would address this issue and a couple of further minor packaging issues.
Unless somebody objects, I intend to apply this patch in near future.
